               <msContents>
                  <summary>The second of three volumes of a <title>Dīvān</title> of Ḥāfiẓ (ca.
                     1315–1390), together with together with <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26520"><idno>Persian MS 1001</idno></ref> and
                     <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26522">1003</ref>. Purchased by Manchester's Chetham Library in circa <date
                        calendar="#Gregorian" when="1800">1800</date>, then-librarian <persName
                        role="trl" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/92189357" key="person_92189357">John
                        Haddon Hindley</persName> references these volumes in his English
                     translations of select ghazals.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_1002-item1">
                     <author key="person_56731778" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/56731778/"
                        change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ḥāfiẓ, 14th
                           cent.</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Ḥāfiẓ Shīrāzī</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Shams al-Dīn Muḥammad
                           Shīrāzī</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">حافظ شيرازى</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName>شمس الدین محمد شیرازی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20666" change="#ids-cleanup"
                        >Dīvān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20666" change="#ids-cleanup">دیوان</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmalla"/>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <colophon/>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>In his appendix to his translation, p. iii, Hindley explictly describes
                        this manuscript as "purchased into the Chetham Library after these Papers
                        were prepared for the Press..." provides a catalogue description on p. ix,
